This situation is ongoing. It involves the property at 8989 Beach St. Balfour B.C. The property is 13.41 acres in size. with waterfront on Kootenay Lake. The owner has a motor home park on the lakefront with approx.8-10 units parked there for the entire summer. There is also a double wide mobile home which is rented out. Behind the motor homes is a wetland. A habitat for Great Blue Heron, ducks, frogs, coyote, etc. This spring the owner used heavy machinery in the area to disturb the perimeter of the water channel, squashing who knows how many eggs and nests. Since the summer heat has arrived we can smell sewage. We wonder where the sewage from all those homes is going, and suspect it is contaminating the wetland. We have 6 breeding heron pairs feeding there. 

